  "text": "The above-described studies mostly refer to quasi-static tests, while the number of described research studies on composites subjected to fatigue loading is very limited. Obviously, the fatigue processes have cumulative character of damage evolution, and these processes were divided into three phases of damage evolution, which has a reflection in the character of the temperature and AE events evolution [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . Following this, the classification of damage types occurring during these processes are possible using similar approaches as for quasi-static tests.",
